        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 5:54PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sulligent, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Detroit, Henson Springs, Weston, Sulligent, Byrd, Pine Springs,
Hamilton, Bexar, Shottsville, and Rankin Fite Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
